  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Weapon Preference: Railguns and Missiles<o:p></o:p><=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Amon'krie</span> are small
  worm-like beings just under 2 meters long. They propel their bodies by
  undulating their underside.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span=
>They
  have several small tubules near their head which they use to grasp tools.
  They prefer to make their homes under the ice of a planet and have very p=
oor
  eyesight. Their average lifespan is about 50 years.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The <span class=3DSpellE>Amon'krie</span> have a soc=
iety
  made up of several groups of governing personnel. Each group has absolute
  authority over a different sector of their government.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>They work together in a delicate network of checks a=
nd
  balances. Their society is strongly xenophobic and does not interact well
  with other races. The <span class=3DSpellE>Amon'krie</span> are thought t=
o have
  evolved on a planet far on the rim of the galaxy.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>They developed spaceflight relatively quickly, but f=
ound
  no other sentient life near them.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;
  </span>Over the centuries, they developed the belief that theirs was the =
only
  race in <span class=3DSpellE>existance</span>. As they ventured further i=
nto
  the galaxy, they did finally encounter other species.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Unfortunately their isolation had already left them
  strongly xenophobic.</p>
